snippet.title: Lesson 28 - Service Design Patterns
snippet.description: In this lesson Mark Richards  “opens up and looks under the hood” inside a service (microservice or macro service) and describes 2 different design patterns - the direct access design and the api access design. Mark explains each of these design patterns and then shows why the api access design pattern is a much better way to design a service. Stay tuned each Monday for more lessons in Software Architecture at https://www.developertoarchitect.com/lessons/.
